lexer:
The lexical rules of language in ANTLR: 
 lexer grammar RCLLangLexer; 
 FORWARD     :'forward'; 
 BACKWARD    :'backward'; 
 TURNRIGHT   :'turnright'; 
 TURNLEFT    :'turnleft'; 
 APPROACH    :'approach'; 
 GRASP       :'grasp';
 BACK_TO_USER    :'back_to_user';

 ID          : [a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z_0-9]*; 
 NUMBER      : '-'?[0-9]+ ('.' [0-9]+)?; 
 COMMA       : ','; 
 SEMI        : ';'; 
 WS          : [ 	
]+ -> skip; 
 COMMENT : '#' .*? (''? '
' | EOF) -> skip;

parser:
The syntactic rules of language in ANTLR: 
 parser grammar RCLLangParser; 
 options { tokenVocab=RCLLangLexer; } 
 program         : command+; 
 command         : (forwardCommand | backwardCommand | turnrightCommand | turnleftCommand | approachCommand | graspCommand | backCommand) SEMI; 
 forwardCommand  : FORWARD NUMBER; 
 backwardCommand : BACKWARD NUMBER; 
 turnrightCommand: TURNRIGHT NUMBER; 
 turnleftCommand : TURNLEFT NUMBER; 
 approachCommand : APPROACH ID; 
 graspCommand    : GRASP ID;
 backCommand     : BACK_TO_USER;
